{
  "texts": [
    "The Q = 0 constraintConsider a ground state in the w-twisted sector for odd w, [|Φ w ⟩] σ w. We saw in (2.8) that such a state, if physical, must satisfy Q n [|Φ w ⟩] σ w = 0 for all n ≥ 0.",
    "Q is a weight 3 gauge field, so in vertex operator language, this translates toQ(z)V w m 1,m 2 (x i; z i) = O((z -z i) -2),where we recall the relationship between [|Φ w ⟩] σ w and V w m 1,m 2 (3.11).",
    "We can, however, determine precisely what the OPE of any of the free fields with this vertex operator is purely from the representation theory [7], as we did with ξ α (z) in (3.9).",
    "Strictly speaking, we do not need to work at the level of the free field realisation and only need the OPE of the supercurrents with V w m 1,m 2, the spectrally flowed highest weight states.",
    "To be explicit for our purposes here,ξ + (z)[|Φ w ⟩] σ w = r∈Z+1/2 z -r-1/2 ξ + r [|Φ w ⟩] σ w = z -w+1 2 | Φw ⟩ σ w + O(z -w-1 2), χ ± (z)[|Φ w ⟩] σ w = r∈Z+1/2 z -r-1/2 χ ± r [|Φ w ⟩] σ w = χ ± -1 2 ± w 2 |Φ w ⟩ σ w + O(z),where| Φw ⟩ = χ - -w-1 2 ψ - -w-1 2 • • • χ - -1 ψ - -1 χ - 0 ψ - 0 |m 1, m 2 + 1/2⟩.Therefore, recalling (2.4), we deduce thatS +++ S +-+ (z)V w m 1,m 2 (x i; z i) ∼ O((z -z i) -w-1)."
  ]
}